# doc-anchors-validate (.salpignore) — anchor-systems benchmark fixtures.
#
# These directories hold INTENTIONAL SALP test inputs, not real cross-references.
# The turn-end SALP hook must not flag them as repo defects.
#
# salp-short/ — system under test: namespace-free [ANC:id] / [REF:id] form
#   (README "salp-short"); rejected by the grammar by design, so every token
#   here is reported as "malformed" unless skipped.
salp-short/
#
# corrupted/ — deliberately planted graph anomalies for the `linting` variant
#   (dead ref [REF:api:oauth-callback], duplicate anchors). It is a corrupted
#   COPY of salp/, so its anchors also collide with salp/'s as "duplicates".
corrupted/
